<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0286 </DOCNO><TEXT>Following the events at Chernobyl, the British Government and the nuclearengineering industries have undertaken a critical review of safety analysesand also of the measures planned in the event of an accident in a commercialnuclear power plant. In general terms, the measures are considered tobe adequate and the need to introduce major changes has not arisen. Areview of emergency plans has led to the result that minor differencesexisted between the plans for different plants, and in the meantime,these have been eliminated.</TEXT></DOC>